Flask Inventory Management Application
Setup Instructions
1. Install Dependencies
Create a requirements.txt file with:

Flask==3.0.0
Flask-SQLAlchemy==3.1.1
Install dependencies:

bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
2. Project Structure
Create the following structure:

inventory_app/
â”œâ”€â”€ app.py
â”œâ”€â”€ requirements.txt
â””â”€â”€ templates/
    â”œâ”€â”€ base.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ index.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ products.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ product_form.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ locations.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ location_form.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ movements.html
    â”œâ”€â”€ movement_form.html
    â””â”€â”€ report.html
3. Run the Application
bash
python app.py
The application will be available at http://127.0.0.1:5000/

4. Sample Data Setup
Once the application is running, follow these steps to create sample data:

Create Products:
Go to Products â†’ Add New Product
Create the following:
Product A (ID: PROD_A, Name: "Laptop")
Product B (ID: PROD_B, Name: "Monitor")
